  "prompt": "Where would the priority of making Area 51 files public fall if Clinton wins?",
  "response": "The priority of making Area 51 files public would likely depend on various factors, including the broader political agenda, public opinion, and the specific goals of a hypothetical Clinton administration. Former President Bill Clinton did express some interest in declassifying information related to UFOs and the military in the past, which could suggest that a similar approach might be taken by a future President Hillary Clinton.\n\nHowever, it\u2019s essential to consider that national security concerns, ongoing intelligence operations, and the opinions of military and security advisors would play significant roles in such decisions. Therefore, while there might be some movement towards transparency regarding Area 51 and related files, it would not necessarily be a top priority compared to more pressing national issues.\n\nUltimately, the extent to which any administration would pursue the declassification of such files could be influenced by public interest, media attention, and the political climate at the time.",
